.TH HOME-APPLIANCES 1 "2026-04-19" "1.0.0" "Home Appliances CLI"
.SH NAME
home-appliances \- control home appliances from the command line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B home-appliances
[\fIOPTION\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIIP\fR] [\fIARGS\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B home-appliances
is a command-line tool for controlling home appliances on the local network.
It supports Gree air conditioner units (UDP port 7000, AES-128-ECB, LAN v2 protocol),
Roborock robot vacuum cleaners, Samsung smart TVs, and Brother network printers.
.PP
Devices are discovered on the
.B 192.168.1.0/24
subnet and their addresses are cached in the user configuration directory.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS General
.TP
.B version
Print the program version and exit.
.TP
.B help
Print a help summary and exit.
.SS AC (Gree)
.TP
.BI "ac list"
Discover and list all Gree AC units on the local network.
Stores found devices for later use.
.TP
.BI "ac bind " IP
Bind to the Gree AC unit at the given
.I IP
address and store the device key for subsequent commands.
.TP
.BI "ac status " IP
Print the full status of the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "ac temp " IP
Print the current target temperature of the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "ac on " IP
Turn the AC unit at
.I IP
on.
.TP
.BI "ac off " IP
Turn the AC unit at
.I IP
off.
.TP
.BI "ac set " IP " " TEMP
Set the target temperature of the AC unit at
.I IP
to
.I TEMP
degrees Celsius.
.TP
.BI "ac swing-v " IP " " MODE
Set vertical swing mode of the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.I MODE
is one of:
.BR default ,
.BR fixed ,
.BR full ,
.BR top ,
.BR mid-top ,
.BR mid ,
.BR mid-bot ,
.BR bot .
.TP
.BI "ac swing-h " IP " " MODE
Set horizontal swing mode of the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.I MODE
is one of:
.BR default ,
.BR fixed ,
.BR full ,
.BR left ,
.BR mid-left ,
.BR mid ,
.BR mid-right ,
.BR right .
.TP
.BI "ac xfan " IP " " STATE
Enable or disable the xfan feature on the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.I STATE
is
.B on
or
.BR off .
.TP
.BI "ac health " IP " " STATE
Enable or disable the health (ionizer) feature on the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.I STATE
is
.B on
or
.BR off .
.TP
.BI "ac air " IP " " STATE
Enable or disable the fresh air feature on the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.I STATE
is
.B on
or
.BR off .
.TP
.BI "ac antifrost " IP " " STATE
Enable or disable the anti-frost protection on the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.I STATE
is
.B on
or
.BR off .
.TP
.BI "ac unit " IP " " UNIT
Set the temperature display unit on the AC unit at
.IR IP .
.I UNIT
is
.B celsius
or
.BR fahrenheit .
.SS Vacuum (Roborock)
.TP
.BI "vacuum status " IP
Print the current status of the robot vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum consumables " IP
Print the consumable levels (brush, filter, etc.) of the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum start " IP
Start a full cleaning run on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum stop " IP
Stop the current cleaning run on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum pause " IP
Pause the current cleaning run on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum dock " IP
Send the vacuum at
.I IP
back to its docking station.
.TP
.BI "vacuum spot " IP
Start a spot-cleaning run on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum find " IP
Play a locate sound on the vacuum at
.I IP
to help find it.
.TP
.BI "vacuum fan " IP " " LEVEL
Set the fan speed level on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.I LEVEL
is one of:
.BR silent ,
.BR balanced ,
.BR turbo ,
.BR max .
.TP
.BI "vacuum reset-main " IP
Reset the main brush consumable counter on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum reset-side " IP
Reset the side brush consumable counter on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum reset-filter " IP
Reset the filter consumable counter on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "vacuum reset-sensor " IP
Reset the sensor consumable counter on the vacuum at
.IR IP .
.SS TV (Samsung)
.TP
.BI "tv probe " IP
Probe the Samsung TV at
.I IP
and print device information.
.TP
.BI "tv key " IP " " KEY
Send a remote control key press to the TV at
.IR IP .
.I KEY
is any Samsung remote key name (e.g.
.BR KEY_POWER ,
.BR KEY_VOLUMEUP ).
.TP
.BI "tv volup " IP
Increase the volume by one step on the TV at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "tv voldown " IP
Decrease the volume by one step on the TV at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "tv mute " IP
Toggle mute on the TV at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "tv power " IP
Toggle the power state of the TV at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "tv off " IP
Turn off the TV at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "tv source " IP
Switch the input source on the TV at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "tv hdmi " IP " " NUM
Switch to HDMI input number
.I NUM
on the TV at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "tv channel " IP " " CH
Tune the TV at
.I IP
to channel number
.IR CH .
.SS Printer (Brother)
.TP
.BI "printer probe " IP
Probe the Brother printer at
.I IP
and print device information.
.TP
.BI "printer status " IP
Print the current status of the printer at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "printer toner " IP
Print the toner level of the printer at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "printer pages " IP
Print the page counter of the printer at
.IR IP .
.TP
.BI "printer consumables " IP
Print the consumable levels of the printer at
.IR IP .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output. Additional diagnostic messages are printed to standard error.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the program version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print a help summary and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress all output except errors. When used with
.BR "printer status" ,
exits with status 2 if the printer reports a device error state.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/home-appliances/config
Main configuration file. Stores preferences such as default subnet and logging level.
.TP
.I ~/.config/home-appliances/gree_devices
Cached list of discovered Gree AC units (IP address and device key pairs).
Updated by
.BR "ac list" " and " "ac bind" .
.TP
.I ~/.config/home-appliances/roborock_devices
Cached list of discovered Roborock vacuum cleaners (IP address and token pairs).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error (invalid arguments, network failure, device unreachable, etc.).
.TP
.B 2
Device error state. Only returned by
.B "printer status"
when the
.B \-\-quiet
option is given and the printer reports an error condition.
.SH EXAMPLES
Discover all Gree AC units on the local network:
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances ac list
.EE
.RE
.PP
Bind to an AC unit and then set it to 22 degrees:
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances ac bind 192.168.1.50
home-appliances ac set 192.168.1.50 22
.EE
.RE
.PP
Turn on the AC unit and enable health mode:
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances ac on 192.168.1.50
home-appliances ac health 192.168.1.50 on
.EE
.RE
.PP
Send the robot vacuum to its dock:
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances vacuum dock 192.168.1.70
.EE
.RE
.PP
Check vacuum consumable levels:
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances vacuum consumables 192.168.1.70
.EE
.RE
.PP
Switch the TV to HDMI 2:
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances tv hdmi 192.168.1.80 2
.EE
.RE
.PP
Check printer toner level with verbose output:
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances -v printer toner 192.168.1.90
.EE
.RE
.PP
Check printer status quietly (exit code 2 if printer error):
.PP
.RS
.EX
home-appliances --quiet printer status 192.168.1.90
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gree (7),
.BR avahi-browse (1),
.BR nmap (1)
